1. cs.SI (Social and Information Networks) - The paper studies the behavior of a CTRW on a time varying dynamic graph, which is a common topic in the study of social and information networks. 
2. cs.DS (Data Structures and Algorithms) - The paper discusses the behavior of a CTRW, which is a type of random walk, on a time varying graph. This topic is relevant to the study of data structures and algorithms. 
3. cs.NA (Numerical Analysis) - The paper establishes conditions under which the CTRW is a stationary and ergodic process, which involves numerical analysis techniques. 
4. cs.SY (Systems and Control) - The paper studies the behavior of a CTRW on a dynamic graph, which can be viewed as a system that evolves over time. This topic is relevant to the study of systems and control. 
5. cs.IT (Information Theory) - The paper characterizes the stationary distribution of the CTRW under certain conditions, which involves information theory concepts such as entropy and mutual information.
